california foreign language project page 1 california foreign language project the california foreign language project the california foreign language project cflp is a california subjet matter project csmp professional development program designed to strengthen foreign language instruction at every level of california's educational system the project sponsors a network of nine regional projects for a total of eleven sites that are responsible for hosting professional development programs for language educators in their respective areas these programs support teachers over time and expose them to new developments in the field the fundamental goal of this effort is to improve the overall communication skills of foreign language students while enhancing their understanding of other cultures for additional information duarte m silva executive director california foreign language project 650 736 9042 fax 650 723 7578 duarte silva stanford edu please visit our website cflp regional sites offer year round professional development programs for teachers including institutes in the summer and professional development series during the school year moreover sites sponsor leadership development programs that enable participants to become more intensively involved in advancing california's language teaching reform efforts these initiatives also prepare teachers to assume leadership positions in their schools and districts and to lead professional development activities for their colleagues each of the cflp sites is staffed by a director who collaborates with a faculty advisor from the hosting campus additionally each site is supported by a local leadership team composed of teacher leaders who have demonstrated expertise and leadership in designing and implementing professional development programs all of the cflp sites have established partnerships with low performing districts and schools in order to strengthen the overall literacy skills of students and language programs in these schools especially those designed for heritage speakers and english language learners the projects are also responsible for assisting teachers to effectively use state board adopted instructional materials with their students the project's work is guided by a 15 member advisory board representing all major california educational institutions and a faculty advisor professor amado padilla of the stanford university school of education the project co sponsors the annual summer seminar for foreign language teachers with the california language teachers association and has established a support group to assist with the preparation of california language educators who are pursuing national board certification since its inception the cflp has vigorously pursued the goal of challenging language professionals to improve and expand language programs in california and to promote foreign language education for all students the project aims to involve every language teacher in a supportive professional community that fosters leadership opportunities for promoting and advocating for the retention expansion and articulation of foreign and heritage language offerings across educational levels beginning in the elementary grades project background or contact http www stanford edu group cflp page 2 bay area foreign language program baflp stanford university 520 galvez mall ceras room 135 stanford ca 94305 3084 650 736 9618 fax 650 723 7578 sally mearns site director smearns stanford edu second language instruction of central california slicc csu bakersfield 22 educ 9001 stockdale hwy bakersfield ca 93311 1099 661 398 9036 fax 661 664 2497 patricia rice site director price csub edu southern area international languages network sailn san diego state university san diego county office of education 6401 linda vista road room 621n san diego ca 92111 7399 858 569 5354 fax 858 576 9712 rebecca sapien melchor co director rsapien melchor projects sdsu edu norman leonard co director nleonar